sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TNY2AKUB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A plasmid allowing rtTA-induced expression of the cell-fate regulator Ngn1 linked to an enhanced yellow fluorescent protein reporter, and a red fluorescent protein reporter tethered by a 2A linker. This construct allows for the verification of the 2A linker, with the ideal result of yellow-labeled Ngn1 remaining in the nucleus and red-labeled mKate being exported to the cytoplasm.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM2008 Princeton team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This plasmid was constructed by digesting pLV-TRE-Sox17-Ubc-Bla with SfiI to excise TRE-Sox17, and inserting the PCR SOEd SfiI-Ngn1-linker-EYFP-2A-mKate-SfiI.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the backbone plasmid into which SfiI_Ngn1-linker-EYFP-2A-mKate_SfiI was inserted after digestion with SfiI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cil Purnick
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Constructed by members of the Weiss Lab.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The SfiI restriction site must be used in digesting this plasmid. Sox17 must first be removed before this plasmid can effectively serve as a backbone.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Ngn1 is a transcription factor that promotes the differentiation of embryonic stem cells into neuronal precursors.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Glass
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This gene was obtained from members of the Weiss Lab.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This gene required multiple rounds of verification by sequencing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This short sequence connects the Ngn1 and EYFP gene products, providing a translational fusion. This enables us to detect the location of Ngn1 by tracking the appearance of fluorescent yellow protein within the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Glass
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This linker sequence was provided by Dr. Patrick Guye, a former member of the Weiss Lab.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This linker was added to Ngn1 and EYFP by means of specially-designed PCR primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is an enhanced yellow fluorescent reporter protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Available commercially
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: EYFP can be connected to other gene products by means of a linker sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a protein linker sequence that allows one reporter protein, in our case EYFP, to be linked to another, in our case mKate, under certain conditions and cleaved under certain other conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sequence from publication (annotated)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is described in Osborn et al. "A Picornoviral 2A-Like Sequence-Based Tricistronic Vector Allowing for High-Level Therapeutic Gene Expression Coupled to a Dual-Reporter System." Molecular Therapy, Vol. 12, No. 3, Sept. 2005.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part must be added by means of specially-designed PCR primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a red fluorescent reporter protein, found to be more reliable than MCherry or DsRed2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Available commercially
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Any linker sequence needs to be added by means of specially-designed PCR primers.
